# Anagram Finder
A simple command line utility for finding anagrams in a specified file.

## Software required to run this
* Java 17

## Automated tests 
Automated tests covering various cases are included. 
shouldFindAnagramsFromExample1_txt() is for testing the example1.txt file. Comment out 
shouldFindAnagramsFromExample2_txt() method.
shouldFindAnagramsFromExample2_txt() is for testing the example2.txt file. Comment out 
shouldFindAnagramsFromExample1_txt() method.

## Exceptions handling 
There is Exceptions handling included in the java code e.g. FileNotFoundException

## Big O analysis
The overall running time of this algorithm is O(n log n) because sorting an array of n 
characters takes O(n log n) time.

##Reasons behind data structures chosen
I chose TreeSet<String> to avoid duplication and Arrays for faster performance.

##What would you do given more time
If given more time, I would make the application multi-threaded and spawn a new thread for each 
time anagrams of a certain length are investigated (printAnagramList()). 

This would make the application faster.

## Building and Running the tests
```
./gradlew clean build
```
This will run shouldFindAnagramsFromExample1_txt() for testing the example1.txt file. Comment out 
shouldFindAnagramsFromExample2_txt() method.

## Output of example1.txt 
abc,bac,cba
fun,unf
hello

## Running the program
```
./gradlew bootRun --args="example2.txt" 
```
where example2.txt is the text file that we want to search for anagrams

This will run shouldFindAnagramsFromExample2_txt() for testing the example2.txt file. Comment out 
shouldFindAnagramsFromExample1_txt() method.
